-- Absa, Investec, Northam, Paladin, SABMiller: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 2010-10-07T05:51:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/absa-investec-northam-paladin-sabmiller-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for a
third day, advancing 128.94, or 0.4 percent, to 29,697.98 at the
5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): Copper rose as much as 0.6
percent to $8,310 a metric ton on the London Metal Exchange.
Stock of Anglo, the diversified mining company that makes up
almost 10 percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock index, rose
7.57 rand, or 2.6 percent, to 299.27 rand. Shares in larger
rival  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ) gained 4.26 rand, or 1.9
percent, to 232.26 rand.  Absa Group Ltd.  (ASA SJ): The  South African Reserve Bank 
publishes its Financial Stability Review. Shares of Absa, which
is controlled by Barclays Plc, gained for a second day, adding
1.26 rand, or 0.9 percent, to 135.25 rand.  Standard Bank Group Ltd.  (SBK SJ): Africa’s biggest lender
fell 58 cents, or 0.5 percent, to 109.11 rand.  Nedbank Group Ltd.  (NED SJ): South Africa’s fourth-largest
lender rose 45 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 147.45 rand.  Investec Ltd.  (INL SJ): The private bank and wealth manager
holds its quarterly briefing. The company’s stock was unchanged
at 58.96 rand.  Northam Platinum Ltd.  (NHM SJ): A strike over pay at the
platinum producer’s Zondereinde mine, which has caused losses of
about 250 million rand ($36 million) in revenue so far, is
expected to continue. Stock of Northam rose 9 cents, or 0.2
percent, to 47.98 rand.  Paladin Capital Ltd.  (PLD SJ): The private equity company
controlled by PSG Group Ltd. said profit for the first half
through August declined 29 percent to 96.8 million rand. The
sale of CIC Holdings will result in a cash inflow of around 371
million rand before tax, it said. The shares dropped 19 cents,
or 5.9 percent, to 3.01 rand.  SABMiller Plc  (SAB SJ): The world’s second-largest brewer
by volume is in talks to acquire one of Africa’s biggest brewers
from French liquor company Groupe Castel in a deal worth more
than 6 billion pounds ($9.5 billion), the London-based Times
newspaper reported, without saying where it got the information.
SABMiller’s stock fell 5.76 rand, or 2.6 percent, to 217.64
rand.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Oil rose as much as 0.5 percent to
$83.61 a barrel in electronic trading in New York. Stock of
Sasol, the world’s biggest maker of motor fuel from coal, rose
3.40 rand, or 1.1 percent, to 326.90 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) added 3 percent to $21.66.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 1.1 percent to $47.52. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) climbed 2.6 percent to $67.84. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 4.3 percent to $5.58. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) added 0.8 percent to $15.93. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) rose 0.3 percent to $11.87. Impala Platinum Holdings
Co. (IMPUY US) advanced 3.5 percent to $27.78. Sappi Ltd. (SPP
US) was little changed at $5.18. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) appreciated
1.1 percent to $47.73. Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY US) slid
0.5 percent to $21.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:
